news.title: Kalaburagi gets Karnataka's government nod for taller housing developments
news.para: The state govt's approval on Feb 18 for increasing building height limits addresses a long-standing request from city residents.

news.title: Adani Group to invest Rs 1.1 lakh crore across multiple sectors in Madhya Pradesh
news.para: The Group has already invested over Rs 50,000 crore in Madhya Pradesh across energy, infrastructure, manufacturing, logistics and agri-business, generating more than 25,000 jobs.

news.title: Belagavi civic body to conduct e-khata mela on February 24
news.para: ​Accordingly, it is intended to issue e-Khata to all properties pending within the jurisdiction of urban local bodies in the state within three months. The minimum required documents should be submitted to obtain A and B accounts of the properties.

news.title: Kerala: Of nine lakh documents registered yearly, only 500 done independently
news.para: Since the introduction of the facility on March 1, 2016, through a notification by the inspector general of registrations, only 4,430 documents have been prepared and registered by citizens without the assistance of document writers or advocates.

news.title: Noida authority to e-auction industry plots under new policy soon
news.para: Spread across sectors 7, 8, 10, 62, 80, and 164, these plots will have a total area of around 60,000sqm. Authority officials confirmed that the scheme would be launched anytime soon as most administrative preparations were already complete.

news.title: Alt plans to raise Rs 2,800 crore in 2025
news.para: Following SEBI's SM REIT regulations in 2024, Property Share became the first to secure an SM REIT license in Aug 2024 and listed a Rs 353 crore asset in Dec, marking India's first listed SM REIT.

news.title: E-khatas not capturing full property information, say Bengaluru flat owners
news.para: According to homebuyers, sale deeds usually contain three schedules: Schedule A gives the extent and details of the entire land on which the properties stand, Schedule B mentions the quantity of UDS the buyer is purchasing, and Schedule C has details of the flat being purchased.

news.title: Jaipur development body to announce three more housing schemes this week
news.para: These projects will be established in Mansharampura in Jhotawra, Kardhani in Bassi, and in Bainad in Daulatpura suburbs of the city.

news.title: Maharashtra revenue dept extends deadline for conversion of govt leasehold land to freehold
news.para: In 2019, the govt first came up with a scheme offering a concessional premium for the conversion of Occupancy Class II and leasehold land to freehold.

news.title: PMAY scheme in Kochi caught in imbroglio
news.para: Services of Kudumbashree, the nodal agency, and officials appointed for this purpose will end in March. Corporation lacks a clear plan on how to proceed with the project thereafter.

news.title: Gurugram: 12 years on, no handover yet, Greenopolis homebuyers protest
news.para: Despite multiple complaints to authorities, legal battles in various courts and pleas to ministers, homebuyers remain stuck in limbo, forced to pay EMIs and rent while their homes remain unfinished.

news.title: Mumbai’s redevelopment activity surge sparks rental housing market boom
news.para: The surge in housing society redevelopment across Mumbai has significantly increased rental demand, with average rentals rising 25-30% over the past 12-18 months. Lack of adequate transit accommodation and rising rents are creating affordability concerns for displaced residents, even as developers provide rental allowances.

news.title: Bandra land development is not in CRZ: Centre & Adani Realty informs Bombay HC
news.para: The PILs, filed by activist Zoru Bhathena and Bandra Reclamation Area Volunteers Organisation, said environmental clearance was granted for Bandra-Worli Sea Link under the condition that reclaimed land near it and the toll plaza would not be used for commercial purposes.

news.title: Maharashtra to give additional Rs 50,000 subsidy to PMAY-Rural homes
news.para: The state rural development minister said Chief Minister Devendra Fadnavis has approved decision and provision for the subsidy has been made in the budget for 2025-26.

news.title: HC slams Orris Infrastructure, Union Bank for 'illegal' removal of title deeds
news.para: It has been alleged that without the finalisation of the arbitration proceedings regarding the dispute between these two real estate companies around 40 acres of prime land in Gurgaon, Orris Infrastructure with the "connivance" of bank officials, illegally removed the title papers of the land.

news.title: Hyderabad civic body slaps red notices on 1.5 lakh defaulting commercial establishments
news.para: ​Additionally, the GHMC has served distress warrant notices to 75 properties that have failed to pay their property taxes for up to 10 years.

news.title: Illegal sand mining thrives in absence of clear Maharashtra government policy
news.para: Last week, a team of revenue department officials was attacked by the sand mafia in Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar's Sillod tehsil. The team was trying to stop illegal mining.

news.title: Home minister distributes sanction letters to 20 lakh PMAY beneficiaries
news.para: Hailing Prime Minister Narendra Modi, he said the second phase of PMAY was approved in the first cabinet meeting after the NDA government came to power for a third consecutive term.

news.title: Mumbai: MMRDA gets bids for three BKC plots
news.para: For the recreational plot, M/s Auro Realty Pvt Ltd and M/s Shree Naman Developers Pvt Ltd have thrown their hats in the ring.

news.title: Two FIRs for cheating filed against Chandigarh-based builder
news.para: The complainants, Vikrant Gupta, Raghawendra, Manju Rani, and Pankaj Arora, alleged that the builder cheated them of Rs 1.1 crore on the pretext of making an investment in a project.
